<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/0cbc3dedffdb9ffb813c6289c2163c41.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 9 and b = 3. Calculate:</p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>9.5</li><li>71.6</li><li>18.4</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={9}^{{2}}+{3}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={81}+{9}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={90}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{90}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{9.4868329805051}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{9.5}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arctan{{\left(\frac{{9}}{{3}}\right)}}}\approx{71.565051177078}\approx{71.6}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{71.565051177078}^{\circ}\approx{18.434948822922}\approx{18.4}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

